Strategic Planning  We can provide recommendations of how a client can position itself to take advantage of upcoming market and business trends. Description: Filling teeth without electricity (ART)
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: “Teach a Few to Teach Many” Teethsavers is an organization dedicated to caring for the children of developing countries and their teeth and thereby improving their overall health. Our plan is to educate people,with a high school diploma, in Teethsavers one year school, in developing countries - that can then care for and educate their own people.  The vast numbers of children unable to receive any sort of oral health care in these countries is overwhelming. New techniques of providing oral health care and new methods of education of oral hygiene, have been developed by Teethsavers to facilitate these goals in the absence of normal dental equipment.  The tooth filling, advocated by the World Health Organization (WHO) Atraumatic Restorative Treatment (ART) was developed by Dr. Jo Frencken, MSc, DDS, PhD, the Netherlands during 14 years in Africa and was International Dentist of 1999. Dr. Frencken has been my main consultant since 2000. Graduates of our school in Zambia, Nicaragua, Malawi and Sierra Leone are registered by each countries Medical and Dental Council.  Our organization is the only one teaching full-time ART procedures, no electricity needed and teaching oral hygiene at the children primary school, including mothers and school teacher workshop. We are the fourth category dental school that too many in the world do not know about – Yet.  Easy to move wooden apparatus is locally made and the uniqueness of the apparatus is its simplicity: the child lies on the wooden bench with hers/his head in the lap of the operator while the dental assistant using a wooden table and stool, passes instruments and material in modern four-handed dentistry in a virtually painless process at the patients school. No Tears, No Fears.  Mothers are taught to start daily oral hygiene at age three months (cloth around finger, carefully) and child looking at a picture book, if she cannot read, to develop the child's curiosity. One mother, more literate, teaches the other mothers and follows-up weekly.   Graduates, following the supervised six months field practical, can have a low fee private practice or work for their government. Tooth decay is the most prevalent childhood disease (bacterial infection) in the world. (WHO)

Description: Creates custom social games for brands
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: KBooM! Games is revolutionizing the way we communicate and engage via the rapidly-growing field of social game and app development. We design and build custom games and apps that engage players of all ages in an immersive learning experience. Whether we are designing a game to cleverly teach a concept or a custom game for a familiar brand, KBooM!’s design team zeros in on the core idea and brings it to life on iPad, iPhone, Android and social media platforms.  KBooM! recently launched the Mrs. Judd's Games brand specializing in iPad education games to teach fundamental skills to young children. Collaborating with former kindergarten teacher Frances Judd, the KBooM! development team designs games with elements and ideas children experience in everyday life to create an authentic learning experience in a digital world. Our newest app, Chalk Walk, is the first iPad app to feature pincer grip technology to develop children’s handwriting skills.  We also partner with consumer-facing companies to gamify their brands and create authentic interaction between the brand and its customers. Many in-game branded experiences either interrupt the game to shoehorn in a brand or product, or re-skin existing games with the client’s brand. KBooM!’s process begins with the partner’s marketing challenge and builds a fun interactive expertise that works within a brand’s overall integrated marketing campaign. KBooM! creates entertaining and user-friendly social, casual and mobile games with brands to engage and entertain their customers while deepening relationships. Instead of selling a product at the consumer, we seamlessly integrate brand-relevant images, themes, actions and rewards into the game, creating an opportunity for real-time feedback and rewards for the consumer.   KBooM!’s Chicago offices recently moved to the new 1871 startup space, and our development team is based in Qingdao, China.

Description: Minecraft community for discussing the Walt Disney World Magic Kingdom server based exclusively on the Florida attraction.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Since early in 2011, therealduckie and their Cast Members have been recreating Walt Disney World in Orlando, FL. What started as a small, personal project on Reddit’s Creative Server to build the entire Walt Disney World Magic Kingdom (with working rides) has now become a family of servers and members that span the globe. They have had over 100 cast members in their history, working to bring the entire park to life and smiles to their Guest’s faces. As of today, most of the parks & resorts are at a 1:1 ratio (Magic Kingdom is being rebuilt to the latest standards) and includes many extras, resorts, and even “hidden mickeys”. With experience working in the park, plus close proximity to Walt Disney World, their Cast has extensive knowledge of the inner workings, back stage areas, and guest favorites in ALL the parks. The attention to detail given to mcMagic ranges from specific food choices in restaurants to making sure every water fountain and trash can is in the right place. As Walt Disney said on Opening day: ”May Walt Disney World bring Joy and Inspiration and New Knowledge to all who come to this happy place … a Magic Kingdom where the young at heart of all ages can laugh and play and learn — together.”
